                    <comment id="12504152" author="hossman" created="Wed, 13 Jun 2007 08:53:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;i don&apos;t know much about french, but a few comments...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) &quot;stopwords&quot; seems like an odd name for what i would think of as a &quot;prefix&quot; .. you may want an example in the javadocs to make it clear.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) are Elison&apos;s always lowercase?  I imagine there should be an ignoreCase option just like StopFilter has.  (note that toLowerCase() is hardcoded in the next() method, but nothing ensures that the stopwords list is lowercased)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3) are there any other characters that can appear between an elision and it&apos;s root word besides &apos;\&apos;&apos; ? (i&apos;m particularly wondering about other unicode characters that look like byte 0x27 but are not actually 0x27)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4) this probably doesn&apos;t need to be in it&apos;s own contrib.  contrib/analyzers should be fine .... if Elison&apos;s are specific to french, then contrib/analyzers/src/java/org/apache/lucene/analysis/fr/ makes the most sense, otherwise it might make sense to add a new subpackage under analysis ... &quot;linguistics&quot; perhaps (in contrast to the existing &quot;ngram&quot;) ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
